    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Liquid blacking, ink, or any like substance, such as octopus ink. Specifically refers to black coloring in ancient Rome. The Romans distinguished three principal types of atramentum: librarium, sutorium, and tectorium.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
